      "span_text": "Prior to the MMAS, the only published estimate of the incidence of ED was from a convenience sample of 3250 men aged 26 ± 83 y visiting a preventive medicine clinic in Texas between 1987 and 1991.  Johannes et al 9 has recently reported age-category speci®c incidence rates for ED and shows how they differ by sociodemographic status (education, income) and also health status."
